since my last cut, my hair grew to belly button-length! I decided to get a medium-length blunt cut and curtain bangs to keep my hair healthy and thick these winter months. wdyt? subtle but so pretty. 💇🏽‍♀️✨

Good morning, now say it back! 🧡🧼 & yes, @myceremonia sunday reset duo is @fromthelobby 

I recently got the opportunity to try ceremonia’s papaya scalp scrub that felt absolutely amazing! The pink salt to exfoliate & help balance my scalp’s oil & buildup in the cold months was chef’s kiss. 💋 while  the guava leaf & prickly pear cactus extracts infused my strands and scalp with the moisture she so desperately needs. Then I topped my hair off with mascarilla de babassu (a conditioning hair mask) for an extra punch of moisture. I plan to supplement these two in a couple times a month, in lieu of my normal shampoo + conditioner combo. Feeling revitalized by this gentle and clean detox duo. 💪🏽

If you’re looking for a fun and unique stay in San Francisco, I recommend checking out Hotel Zephyr. The hotel is situated in the historic and charming Fisherman’s Wharf neighborhood. Boasting waterfront views and a campy shipyard theme — there’s plenty to do at #HotelZephyr. Play huge table games, view fun art, and enjoy s’mores every evening!

⚓️ Fisherman’s Wharf hit list ⭐️ (bookmark for your next trip!)

Did you know? This district is home to many family-friendly activities. 

🥣 Eat a bowl of clam chowder at the wharf – while watching sourdough bread bowls get made – 
🚢 stop by Pier 39 for endlessly fun activities - rides, eateries, docked ships and more!
🕺🏽 try the 2 for 1 bundle at the Ripley’s Believe It Or Not museum & Madam Tussaud’s Wax Museum. 
🍫 or roam around Ghirardelli Square and sample some delicious Ghirardelli chocolates with hot cocoa!

🏨 If you need hotel reccs I stayed at both @hotelzephyrsf and @hotelcazasf which were centrally located and where I booked 2 amazing 2-night stays!

Embarked on a monstrous adventure with my bestie to the Asian Art Museum’s Murakami Exhibit: Monsterized! 🎨👹 Murakami’s art isn’t just fun and games; it’s a deep dive into human behavior, with a playful twist. Get ready to encounter the yōkai (ghosts, demons, monsters, shapeshifters, tricksters, and other kinds of supernatural beings and mysterious phenomena), and even a cameo from Godzilla himself. From swelling egos to the digital revolution, this exhibit’s got it all! An electrifying blend of history, pop culture, and eye-popping colors, you don’t want to miss! Takashi Murakami is a global pop culture luminary, and his works are more intriguing than they first appear. Book your tickets and dive into the world of #MonsterizedArt (here until feb. 12, 2024)

Last week I narrowly avoided a brush with the law for *criminal* speeding in Arizona—clocked at 96 mph, though I could've sworn it was 76…🫠bIt brought back a local Uber driver's warning: "You go to Arizona on vacation, but you leave on probation,” and 🦆 if that wasn't me in that moment. I maintain my innocence, and left with a warning. Amid all that, I had the privilege of celebrating my cousin's graduation and explored the stunning Antelope Canyon and Horseshoe Bend with Mom. So I’ll say the trip was a success and one for the books! 🤍
